{"lemma":"نَصْرانِيّاتٌ","slug":"نَصْرانِيّاتٌ","root":"ن.ص.ر","root_slug":"ن-ص-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ص-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نَصْرانِيّ","root":"نصر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":15},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39920"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%92%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"Christian"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"Nazarene","tags":["obsolete","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a Christian","examples":[{"text":"مَا كَانَ إِبْرَاهِيمُ يَهُودِيًّا وَلَا نَصْرَانِيًّا وَلَٰكِنْ كَانَ حَنِيفًا مُسْلِمًا","english":"Neither was Abraham a Jew nor a Christian but rather he was an upright Muslim"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a Nazarene","tags":["obsolete","rare"],"examples":[{"text":"وَجَدْنَا هَذَا الْمُتَّهَمَ مُخَرِّباً، يُثِيرُ الْفِتْنَةَ بَيْنَ جَمِيعِ الْيَهُودِ فِي الْبِلادِ كُلِّهَا، وَهُوَ يَتَزَعَّمُ مَذْهَبَ النَّصَارَى","english":"We found this accused man to be a saboteur, stirring up discord among all the Jews in the entire land. He spearheads the sect of the Nazarenes."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Relative adjective (nisba) composed of نَاصِرَة (nāṣira) + ـَانـ (-ān-) + ـِيّ (-iyy), based on a modified form of النَّاصِرَة (an-nāṣira, “Nazareth”). Compare Hebrew נוֹצְרִי (nots'rí) and Classical Syriac ܢܵܨܪܵܝܵܐ (nāṣrāyā)."},"ipa":["/nasˤ.raː.nijj/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39920","headword_ar":"نَصْرَانِىٌّ","root":"nSr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoraAnN","text_ar":"نَصْرَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A,) or this latter has not been used without the addition of the relative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or it has been sometimes used, (M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoriY~N","text_ar":"نَصْرِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) but we have not heard this used, (M,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A Christian:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or this is a secondary application, and the original meaning is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a Nazarene:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoraAniy~apN","text_ar":"نَصْرَانِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoraAnapN","text_ar":"نَصْرَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) or the latter is used only by poetic licence: (IB:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaAraY","text_ar":"نَصَارَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Christians"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a rel. n. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASirapu","text_ar":"نَاصِرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or Nazareth,] a town of Syria, (S, M, K,) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoraAnapu","text_ar":"نَصْرَانَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, IDrd, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoraAnu","text_ar":"نَصْرَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSuwriyapN","text_ar":"نَصُورِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Sgh, K,) without teshdeed, accord. to Sgh, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSoriY~N","text_ar":"نُصْرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSoraY","text_ar":"نُصْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in a copy of the M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoraY","text_ar":"نَصْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSorawapu","text_ar":"نَصْرَوَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) so originally, and then applied to such as hold the religion of its inhabitants: (Msb:) this is the opinion of the lexicologists; but it is of weak authority, though admissible as there are other anomalous rel. ns.: (M:) or [so in K, but in the S, and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaAraY","text_ar":"نَصَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoriY~N","text_ar":"نَصْرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kh, M, Msb, K,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mahaAraY","text_ar":"مَهَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mahoriY~N","text_ar":"مَهْرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;) or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoraAnN","text_ar":"نَصْرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kh, S, M) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoraAnapN","text_ar":"نَصْرَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadaAmaY","text_ar":"نَدَامَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadomaAnN","text_ar":"نَدْمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kh, S, M) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadomaAnapN","text_ar":"نَدْمَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) but more probably of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoraAnN","text_ar":"نَصْرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because this word has been sometimes used, whereas we have not heard"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoriY~N","text_ar":"نَصْرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"used: (M:) and it is implied in the copies of the K, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoSaArN","text_ar":"اَنْصَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoraAniY~N","text_ar":"نَصْرَانِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but correctly, it is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSoraAnN","text_ar":"نَصْرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is said in the TS, and the L, in both of which is mentioned the saying of the poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"lam~aA raA^ayotu nabaTFA A^anoSaAraA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When I saw Nabatheans, Christians"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaAraY","text_ar":"نَصَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","A","S","Msb","K","IB","Lth","IDrd","Sgh","TA","Kh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}